  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Monte Rosa region offers wonderful walks at every level from gently scenic strolls like 'The Queen's Walk' to longer, more challenging hikes such as the all-day 'Walser Path', all passing through unspoilt miles of sensational scenery. Further highlights include the picturesque 'Valley of the Princes', the Valdobbia Waterfall, and the popular little Blue Lake and Green Lake, coloured by melting waters from the glacier. On your arrival in Gressoney, your Inghams Representative will have a full programme of walks and activities available for you to choose from, and on the right are two free guided walks to introduce you to the Monte Rosa area<br /><br /><br /><strong>Inghams Guided Wanderwalks</strong></p>
<p>Here are some great examples of introductory walks around the area of Gressoney. On arrival in Gressoney your Inghams Representative will have a full programme of walks and activities to choose from whether you are a holiday rambler or like more challenging hikes.</p>
<p><strong>The River Lys</strong> | Easy | Approx 3 hrs |<br />The River Lys runs along the Ayas Valley and through Gressoney La Trinité to Gressoney St Jean. This gentle walk takes you along the river banks, passing through traditional small ‘Walser’ hamlets and villages, a verdant flowerfilled meadow and sheltered woodland – a perfect walk to get to know the lower valley and its villages.</p>
<p><strong>Lake Gabiet</strong> | Easy | Approx 1 hr |<br />This stunning walk is great for finding your bearings at the top of the Staffal Gabiet gondola-lift. Once at the top, stunning Lake Gabiet is only 20 minutes walk away, across a lush green open plateau. Our route also passesa convenient mountain refuge, where you can enjoy refreshments and admire the impressive backdrop of the Monte Rosa Massif.</p>
<p><em>Please note: Walks are available on a first come first served basis and also subject to weather conditions. Please register with your Rep on arrival.</em></p>]]></walkingDescription>
